uk.ac.ed.epcc.webapp.model.data

Interface Removable

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    BadKeyFactory.BadKey, FileData, LogFactory.Entry, MessageData, TextData

    public interface Removable
    Interface for DataObjects that can be removed from a DataObjectFactory.FilterIterator Classes that implement this should therefore have a well defined iteration order that won't per permuted if elements from the start of the sequence are removed. It is also implemented by the target classes of Log Entry If this interface is implemented the class provides a method to be called when the parent Entry is deleted.
